The physics implemented here is public knowledge and is not claimed by anyone:

  Yee, K.S. (1966), "Numerical solution of initial boundary value problems
    involving Maxwell's equations in isotropic media" -- the FDTD scheme.
  Wolf, E. (1969), "Three-dimensional structure determination of semi-transparent
    objects from holographic data" -- the Fourier Diffraction Theorem.
  Devaney, A.J. (1982), "A filtered backpropagation algorithm for diffraction
    tomography" -- the inversion this rests on.
  Born, M. & Wolf, E., "Principles of Optics" -- the approximation, and its limits.

These are laws and algorithms, not code. The implementation is original and MIT.
